Soak bulgur in 1/3 cup hot water 1 hour. Combine bulgur, lamb, beef, onion, garlic, mint, curry paste, cumin, allspice, and coriander. Chill, covered, 30 minutes. Mix cucumber, yogurt, and pepper in small bowl. Season with salt. Preheat grill to medium-high. Shape meat mixture into 12 balls and flatten into thick miniburgers. Season with salt. Grill patties 4 to 8 minutes, turning once, until thermometer inserted registers 160 degrees F. Wrap each patty in a lettuce leaf and serve with yogurt sauce and tomato.